Jeff Bezos had been losing patience with The Washington Post=E2=80=99s
liberal predilection long before he mandated a purely pro-markets Opinion s=
ection, and even before endorsement-gate. In fact, the tensions that culmin=
ated in Opinion editor David Shipley=E2=80=99s resignation had been buildin=
g for years.

