election, Bezos was memorably pilloried by the D.C. media establishment for=
 what appeared to be a callous and brazen capitulation to
<strong>Trump</strong>. Meanwhile, hundreds of thousands of subscribers rep=
ortedly abandoned the paper.<br/><br/>Notably, Bezos=E2=80=99s only regret =
at the time seemed to pertain to the timing of the rollout: =E2=80=9CI wish=
 we had made the change earlier than we did, in a moment further from the e=
lection and the emotions around it,=E2=80=9D he wrote in an essay for the p=
aper. =E2=80=9CThat was inadequate planning, and not some intentional strat=
egy.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>In hindsight, the mismanagement of the endorsement d=
ecision actually
foreshadowed the far more significant changes that Bezos made to the <em>Po=
